strategies: Associations via color (e.g.; the eagle has yellow and the digger is yellow); known associations (e.g.; pets eagles are trained to fly onto the padded mitt of it's owner in which the mitt looks similar to that of the saddle); and acronyms (e.g.; Racine + Carmel = RC --> RC car).
easier: Some routes were easier than others based on the associations I assigned them. I mainly focused on the images themselves and not the places; so when I could not assign an association between the images; i could not remember it's associations if there was more than one (e.g. the bear and construction I associated because I believe there is a construction/gardening company with the name "Bear;" but I could not association a bear with anything else).
